OL,6,FMr Brown, 61, the chairman of Bellaghy
OL,7,FWolfe Tones GAA club in Co
OL,8,FLondonderry, was ambushed, kidnapped
OL,9,Fand murdered by loyalist
OL,10,Fparamilitaries as he locked the gates
OL,11,Fof the club in May 1997.
OL,13,FNo-one has ever been convicted of his
OL,14,Fkilling.
OL,16,FSpeaking at Westminster, Ben said:
OL,17,F"The murder of Sean Brown nearly 28
OL,18,Fyears ago was brutal and despicable
OL,19,Fand it has caused deep pain and
OL,20,Fanguish to Mrs Brown, her family, and
OL,21,Fmany in the wider community.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/10
