OL,6,F"These steps will not delay the
OL,7,FGovernment's determination to take the
OL,8,Fnecessary steps to ensure that the
OL,9,Fsystem for dealing with legacy is
OL,10,Fhuman rights compliant and can command
OL,11,Fthe confidence of victims and
OL,12,Ffamilies."
OL,14,FFirst Minister Ms O'Neill said: "At
OL,15,Fthe Court of Appeal, Lady Chief
OL,16,FJustice Keegan was unequivocal in her
OL,17,Fremarks, saying that 'the decision to
OL,18,Frefuse a public inquiry cannot stand
OL,19,Fand is unlawful and in breach of
OL,20,FArticle 2 obligations'.
